vine 1.2.0
prefix: ssm
title: Scout source management
---
[ssm] Generalize scout source onboarding and indexing (planning)
Two Scout commands replace the current per-vendor pattern (a bespoke
fetch_modal_docs.py-shaped script per source, a hand-added tuple in
search.py's DOCS_SOURCES, a manual search.py --update run): a batch mutation
command for as many or as few source operations as the caller needs. Every
caller-provided desired origin URL maps to exactly one source declaration and
never fans out; every operation receives one outcome record. A fetch-bearing
mutation targeting an existing source is an explicit re-fetch request even
when it remains fresh; and a
separate refresh-stale command that re-fetches and re-indexes every
already-registered source whose TTL has expired, replacing today's
read-the-warning-then-copy-the-refresh-command manual loop. Neither command
discovers or follows additional documentation URLs. Both commands need
representation on the CLI and as an MCP tool.
Vine graphs are workspace-authored planning artifacts scout never indexes
today; add them as a first-class chunked corpus alongside spec/notes/
proposals/docs, using structural (per-task) chunking rather than raw word
windows, since a task is already the natural retrievable unit.
-> ssm/design/attempt-diagnostics
-> ssm/design/batch-atomicity
-> ssm/design/chunk-adapters
-> ssm/design/command-surface
-> ssm/design/docs-index-entrypoints
