[ssm/design/source-artifact-path] Design source identity to artifact-path mapping (notstarted)
Given the settled docs source identity and the `resources/<safe-name>` root
constraint, decide the deterministic safe-name mapping, collision behavior,
and path stability rules. Settle what happens to a committed artifact path when
a source display name or origin changes, including publication, move, cleanup,
and recovery behavior. The mapping must never let two source identities share
one live artifact root or let an update/remove affect another source's artifact.
Accept: the owner confirms a total one-to-one identity-to-artifact-path mapping
and an unambiguous rename/update/removal transition for committed snapshots.
-> ssm/design/source-artifact-contract
-> ssm/design/source-registry
