[ssm/design/batch-atomicity] Design source batch commit semantics (notstarted)
The caller invariant requires exactly one source row and one outcome record for
every input URL; it does not itself decide whether a successful row may publish
when another row in the same batch fails. Given the single-row publication
boundary, the owner decides the batch commit and recovery contract for mixed
add/update/remove requests, including outcome terminology for rows that did
not commit and the relation between batch-level failure and per-row outcomes.
The result must never report a row as committed when its declaration, snapshot,
and docs-index membership did not cross the publication boundary together.
Accept: the owner confirms one client-visible batch contract that preserves
one outcome record per input URL and unambiguous recovery after interruption.
-> ssm/design/source-publication-boundary
-> ssm/design/source-registry
