[ssm/design/docs-index-entrypoints] Design the sole docs-index entry point (notstarted)
Given the source publication boundary, define the one permitted path through
which docs chunks are built and published. A generic resources/search.py docs
`--update`, `--rebuild`, missing-CURRENT cold build during a direct CLI query,
or missing-CURRENT cold build during resident-worker startup must never
independently publish docs membership: a direct bypass attempt fails loudly
with the settled public repair path, while papers and workspace index
maintenance remain outside this task's scope. The source control plane is the
sole docs-index writer and routes every docs publication, including recovery
replay and initial index creation, through the source publication boundary.
Define the corresponding sole docs-query health gate too: normal CLI, JSON
CLI, and resident-worker/MCP routes must each resolve docs hits through the
same provenance and health validation before ranking or output. No public
docs-query path may return raw semantic or keyword hits around that gate.
Before legacy conversion, apply the settled pre-cutover bridge contract rather
than silently treating aggregate legacy artifacts as source-bound snapshots.
The implementation migration replaces rather than layers beside the current
generic docs `Corpus` path: after cutover no public docs reader or publisher
uses `.index/docs/CURRENT` as independent truth. Docs reads resolve the master
publication manifest to its referenced index generation; docs versions named by
retained publication manifests are not generic-cleanup candidates.
Before cutover, initial docs availability may be established only by the
settled immutable legacy compatibility publication; generic docs update,
rebuild, and cold-build paths never rebuild mutable aggregate artifacts behind
that bridge. The entrypoint returns its corpus-level compatibility/freshness
metadata with every bridge reply and its migration repair action for rejected
legacy writer calls.
Accept: the owner confirms direct CLI and internal-call behavior that makes an
out-of-boundary docs publication or raw docs query architecturally unavailable
or a fatal, actionable error.
-> ssm/design/legacy-docs-precutover
-> ssm/design/mime-representation
-> ssm/design/source-diagnostics
-> ssm/design/source-hit-provenance
-> ssm/design/source-publication-boundary
