[ssm/design/legacy-docs-migration] Design migration of current pinned docs (notstarted)
The current Modal pin expands one llms.txt URL into hundreds of Markdown pages,
and the current VS Code pin groups two distinct raw Markdown URLs beneath one
ledger record. The settled one-URL model forbids retaining either fan-out under
the new source control plane. The owner decides how the existing Modal and VS
Code coverage enters the new ledger: enumerate one row per retained document,
deliberately reduce coverage to explicitly named resources, or retire a set.
For the chosen shape, define source names, origin URLs, MIME values, artifact
paths, snapshot/provenance migration, index rebuild, and removal of legacy
aggregate records and fetch scripts. Do not let the implementation infer a
catalog rule merely to preserve today’s coverage.
Accept: the owner confirms the exact disposition of every current Modal and VS
Code document before legacy fetchers or aggregate ledger rows are retired.
-> ssm/design/docs-index-entrypoints
-> ssm/design/https-single-url-materialization
-> ssm/design/mime-representation
-> ssm/design/source-artifact-path
-> ssm/design/source-hit-provenance
-> ssm/design/source-publication-boundary
-> ssm/design/source-registry
