[ssm/design/legacy-docs-precutover] Design legacy docs pre-cutover bridge (complete)
Before the control plane owns generic docs entrypoints and before legacy
migration converts aggregate pins, preserve the current pinned Modal and VS
Code corpus as one bounded, read-only legacy compatibility publication. The
control plane creates an immutable master publication manifest referencing the
then-current aggregate docs index generation and records its aggregate source
freshness state as compatibility metadata, not as source-bound snapshots. All
direct docs CLI queries and resident-worker startup resolve that master pointer;
there is no raw fallback scan or cold rebuild from mutable aggregate paths.

The bridge labels every docs reply with a corpus-level legacy compatibility
warning and any applicable aggregate freshness warning. It never claims that a
hit has per-source/snapshot provenance. Once the bridge exists, legacy vendor
fetch scripts and generic docs `--update`/`--rebuild` paths fail loudly with the
settled migration repair action rather than mutate aggregate artifacts behind
the published bridge. A missing or invalid bridge publication is
control-plane-fatal. The first fully source-bound publication created by legacy
migration atomically replaces the bridge; only then may bridge data and legacy
writer paths be reclaimed. This task does not decide the eventual document
coverage or migration disposition; ssm/design/legacy-docs-migration owns that.
Accept: existing docs remain queryable only through an explicitly labeled
master-published compatibility snapshot until cutover; no pre-cutover generic
docs update, rebuild, cold build, or legacy fetch silently bypasses the sole
docs writer or presents aggregate legacy hits as source-bound snapshots.
> Use a bounded read-only legacy compatibility publication, not temporary docs unavailability.
> Attach a corpus-level legacy compatibility warning; do not claim per-source/snapshot provenance for aggregate hits.
> After bridge installation, legacy fetchers and generic docs update/rebuild paths fail with the migration repair action.
> The first fully source-bound publication atomically replaces the bridge.
---
[ssm/design/legacy-docs-query-cutover] Design legacy docs query cutover (notstarted)
Current docs hits and freshness warnings derive from aggregate rows and ids
without the source/snapshot provenance required by the new docs health gate.
Before legacy migration changes the docs ledger or index, apply the settled
bounded compatibility bridge until the first fully source-bound publication
atomically replaces it. Settle the health contract for retained legacy docs
during that transition, the exact cutover point, and removal of temporary
reader behavior. No public docs query may silently mix aggregate legacy hits
with source-bound health validation.
Accept: the owner confirms how current docs remain queryable or are deliberately
retired during transition, and that after cutover no legacy aggregate reader or
unprovenanced docs hit path remains.
-> ssm/design/docs-index-entrypoints
