[ssm/design/fresh-source-refetch] Define direct fresh-source refetch behavior (notstarted)
Given the settled source-operation identity, a fetch-bearing add or update
targeting an existing source is an explicit re-fetch request even when its TTL
has not expired. A remove is target-only and never fetches. That behavior
belongs to the existing batch mutation command; it does not add a third public
command. refresh-stale remains the unattended maintenance path and selects
only stale or absent sources. A registered source with no live snapshot is
absent, so refresh-stale selects it without needing a TTL timestamp. The result
tells command-surface and control-plane work how to distinguish an explicit
re-fetch from automatic stale maintenance in their outcomes.
Accept: the owner confirms that a fetch-bearing direct mutation re-fetches a
fresh source, a remove does not, and refresh-stale does not re-fetch fresh
snapshots.
-> ssm/design/source-registry
> A fetch-bearing add or update targeting an existing source is re-fetched even when fresh.
> refresh-stale remains stale/absent-only; no third public command is added.
> A registered source with no live snapshot is absent and refresh-stale selects it.
