[ssm/design/vine-chunking] Design per-task chunking for vine files (complete)
Given the chunk-type-adapter interface from ssm/design/chunk-adapters, design
vine's adapter: parse a .vine file into its task blocks (reusing bacchus's
vine semantics only as far as a structural split needs: use the declared
delimiter when present, otherwise `---`, then recognize task and ref headers.
The indexer must not need a live MCP vine_read call or a full VINE parser.
Apply the bounded task representation settled in ssm/design/vine-task-length.
Task citations are
`<repo-relative-vine-path>#<task-id>#vine`, retaining an unambiguous file
locator plus task id so a result can resolve through the settled
repository-owned citation resolver even when VINE stems collide. This is the
task resolver citation, not necessarily the unique index identity: long-task
segments use distinct adapter index identities while sharing the one task
citation. Ref blocks emit chunks as `<repo-relative-vine-path>#ref:<id>#vine`;
their repository-owned resolution and test contract is designed in
ssm/design/vine-citation-resolution rather than treating a ref proxy as a task.
A ref chunk contains only its local proxy name and description; the referred
VINE is independently discovered and indexed, with no derived target content
and no duplicated child-task text.
-> ssm/design/chunk-adapters
-> ssm/design/vine-task-length
> Parse locally by splitting on a declared delimiter, or the default `---`, then recognizing task and ref headers; do not require a full VINE parser or live MCP call.
> Emit each task segment with a unique adapter index identity and the shared task resolver citation `<repo-relative-vine-path>#<task-id>#vine`.
> Emit ref chunks as `<repo-relative-vine-path>#ref:<id>#vine`; resolve them through the settled ref-aware citation contract rather than task lookup.
> A ref chunk indexes only its local proxy name and description; the target VINE is independently discovered and indexed without derived ref content.
