[ssm/design/vine-corpus] Decide where vine chunks attach in search.py (complete)
VINE chunks belong to the workspace corpus. They are workspace-authored planning
text with the same provenance and trust contract as human-owned spec, notes,
proposals, and root docs; a fourth index would create another routing and
publication state without a distinct reader guarantee. Workspace search ranks
VINE task/ref chunks alongside that writing, while tags preserve their explicit
resolver citations so a result remains distinguishable from prose chunks.

Discovery is a deterministic workspace glob: root `*.vine` plus
`proposals/**/*.vine`, excluding no file by name. The root VINE and proposal
graphs therefore index without a code change; later VINE locations require an
explicit discovery-glob addition rather than an unbounded filesystem scan.
`workspace_chunks()` dispatches discovered VINE files through the `vine-task`
adapter instead of the generic word-window adapter.
Accept: VINE chunks publish only in the workspace index, root and proposal VINE
files are discovered deterministically, and no fourth corpus/routing surface is
introduced.
-> ssm/design/vine-chunking
> VINE chunks are workspace corpus content, not a fourth corpus.
> Discover root *.vine and proposals/**/*.vine deterministically.
> Dispatch discovered VINE files through the vine-task adapter, never generic word windows.
