Before any implementation starts, carefully design and encapsulate the two
invocation surfaces: (1) a ledger CRUD command -- takes a batch of rows
(add/update/remove), each row using the settled target-versus-desired
declaration shape and naming its required MIME when it carries a declaration.
It records mutation intent and drives the corresponding source publication or
removal; it never exposes a declaration change before that publication boundary
completes. The batch reports one outcome per operation and never derives
further URLs; (2)
refresh all sources past their TTL -- no argument, scans and re-fetches only
stale/missing entries, applying its own re-fetch results through the same
publication path.
