[ssm/design/chunk-adapters] Design chunk-type adapters for scout (complete)
Scout's three corpora (papers/docs/workspace) each chunk every source the same
fixed way today: a word-window with overlap, no override. The settled generic
interface is a local `ChunkSource` carrying a local path, local chunk kind, and
resolver citation base, dispatched through a registry from `chunk_kind` to an
adapter. An adapter emits `Chunk` records with a unique `index_id`, embedded
`text`, and canonical serialized `tags`. Tags carry required stable resolver
`citation` plus optional source-pipeline metadata such as source identity and
snapshot generation. `index_id` is unique within its corpus; a `citation` may
be shared by multiple segments of the same resolvable source unit, such as a
long VINE task.

The index writes each record to txtai as `(index_id, text, serialized tags)`;
the tags' authoritative `citation` metadata persists with the index generation.
On loading a published generation, the query path hydrates result citations
from those tags and displays citations rather than raw index ids. The existing
version manifest remains the incremental signature map, but its signature
includes embedded text plus canonical serialized tags so citation/metadata
changes trigger an upsert. A manifest schema change from the current text-only
form requires a full rebuild rather than an incremental update with partially
missing citation metadata.

The default adapter wraps the existing word-window chunker and preserves its
current per-window citation shape. VINE registers as `vine-task`; its long-task
segments receive distinct index ids while retaining the one task citation
settled in ssm/design/vine-chunking. A future PDF-structure, code-AST, or other
structured-source adapter registers through the same interface. This task does
not define a remote source's MIME field or fetch behavior; the source-artifact
contract owns that distinct vocabulary boundary.
Accept: one adapter record and metadata path preserve unique incremental index
identity, stable resolver citation, and metadata-aware signatures before
ssm/design/vine-chunking is finalized against it.
> A registry maps a local chunk_kind to its adapter.
> Chunk is `(index_id, text, tags)`; tags require citation and may carry source-pipeline metadata.
> txtai serialized tags are authoritative metadata; a generation's manifest tracks metadata-aware incremental signatures.
> The default adapter preserves current word-window citations; VINE registers as vine-task.
