[ssm/implement/source-control-plane] Implement the shared source control plane (notstarted)
Implement the settled config reader, docs source orchestration, structured
freshness state, and artifact-to-index lifecycle behind one local control-plane
interface. It consumes the authoritative shared ledger writer and recovery API
from ssm/implement/ledger-access-boundary; command implementations neither
manipulate the ledger nor derive staleness directly. It owns HTTPS fetch
dispatch, including the settled one-URL materialization for every
caller-supplied origin. It provides the common result shape for
control-plane-managed docs sources. Until legacy-docs migration cuts over the
current aggregate pins, those legacy fetchers remain outside this protocol;
ssm/implement/legacy-docs-migration owns their conversion and retirement. No
control-plane-managed source has a direct freshness.stamp mutation bypass.
Before that cutover, implement the settled legacy-docs pre-cutover bridge so
generic docs update, rebuild, and cold-build paths obey its explicit behavior
and legacy vendor fetchers fail with its migration repair action rather than
mutate aggregate artifacts behind it. Enforce the settled remote fetch-admission,
MIME-representation, and fresh-source-
refetch and batch-atomicity policies through this one interface rather than
duplicating concerns in a CLI or MCP wrapper. Respect the settled generic
ledger-access boundary: no operation bypasses the authoritative writer/recovery
protocol for the physical ledger. Construct a query-visible live snapshot only at
complete publication; a staged candidate and an attempt failure must be
unrepresentable as a corpus input or search result. Resolve source health at
that boundary and emit the settled structured diagnostic rather than silently
substituting an invalid snapshot or plain display text. Create, retain, and
clear non-live fetch-attempt diagnostic records according to the settled
attempt-diagnostics contract. At publication, bind every docs chunk to its
source identity and committed snapshot generation or manifest identity; never
publish unbound chunks into the shared docs corpus. Put that binding and the
resolver citation in canonical adapter tags, and force a full docs rebuild when
upgrading the prior text-only manifest schema so no published generation has
partially missing tag metadata.
This is the sole docs-index writer: every generic docs update/rebuild path in
resources/search.py, including a missing-CURRENT cold build from direct CLI or
resident-worker startup, delegates here or fails with the settled fatal repair
path, while paper and workspace index maintenance remain independent.
Replace rather than layer beside the current generic docs corpus publisher:
after cutover public docs reads resolve only the master publication manifest to
its referenced index generation, never `.index/docs/CURRENT`; generic docs
cleanup retains every index/artifact generation referenced by a retained master
publication and may reclaim only unreachable candidates or generations.
Stage source candidates outside the short publication commit lock and apply the
settled automatic rebase procedure when their base publication is stale; never
hold the ledger/publication lock across remote fetches or index construction.
Accept: the control plane is the authoritative path for all registered
one-URL docs sources and can report each row's lifecycle state without a direct
freshness.stamp bypass; every such mutation uses the settled authoritative
ledger boundary, and the generic HTTPS fetcher materializes each admitted
deterministic fixture as exactly one source artifact through that same path.
